@startuml security
!theme cerulean-outline
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowColor #444444
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
skinparam NoteBorderColor #F9A825

title Prana — Security Architecture & Attacker Threat Model

'─────────────────────────────────────────────
' ACTORS
'─────────────────────────────────────────────
actor "Attacker" as ATK #Red
actor "Administrator" as ADM #Green
participant "Browser\n(DevTools)" as BR #LightCoral

'─────────────────────────────────────────────
' AWS AUTH LAYER
'─────────────────────────────────────────────
box "AWS Cognito" #E3F2FD
  participant "User Pool\n<USER_POOL_ID>" as UP
  participant "Identity Pool\n<IDENTITY_POOL_NAME>" as IP
end box

'─────────────────────────────────────────────
' WHAT ATTACKER CAN REACH
'─────────────────────────────────────────────
box "Exposed Attack Surface (IAM scoped)" #FFF3E0
  participant "Timestream\n3 table ARNs only" as TS #Orange
  participant "S3 Bucket\n<S3_BUCKET>\n(PutObject + GetObject)" as S3 #Orange
end box

'─────────────────────────────────────────────
' DEFENSE LAYER 1 — Real-time
'─────────────────────────────────────────────
box "Layer 1 — Real-time Detection (~2 min)" #E8F5E9
  participant "CloudTrail\n<CLOUDTRAIL_NAME>" as CT #Green
  participant "CloudWatch Logs\n/prana/cloudtrail" as CWL #Green
  participant "CW Alarm\n≥50 queries/5min" as CWA #Green
end box

'─────────────────────────────────────────────
' DEFENSE LAYER 2 — Cost kill switch
'─────────────────────────────────────────────
box "Layer 2 — Cost Kill Switch ($5)" #E8F5E9
  participant "AWS Budget\n$5 Timestream guard" as BUD #Green
  participant "IAM Emergency Deny\n<DENY_POLICY>" as DENY #Green
end box

'─────────────────────────────────────────────
' RESPONSE
'─────────────────────────────────────────────
box "Automated Response" #E8F5E9
  participant "SNS\n<SNS_TOPIC>" as SNS #Green
  participant "Lambda\n<LAMBDA_NAME>" as LAM #Green
end box

'═════════════════════════════════════════════
' SEQUENCE
'═════════════════════════════════════════════

== Step 1 — Authentication (legitimate) ==

ATK -> BR : Opens app, logs in\nwith valid credentials
BR -> UP : authenticateUser(email, password)
UP --> BR : idToken (TTL: 1h)\naccessToken (TTL: 1h)\nrefreshToken (TTL: 30 days)
BR -> IP : Exchange idToken for\nAWS STS credentials
IP --> BR : AccessKeyId\nSecretAccessKey\nSessionToken\n(TTL: **1 hour hard limit**)

note over BR #FFF9C4
  **Credentials visible in:**
  • DevTools → Network → Authorization header
  • Browser memory (sessionStorage)
  • Any HTTP proxy / Burp Suite
end note

== Step 2 — What attacker extracts ==

ATK -> BR : Opens DevTools\nCopies STS credentials
note over ATK #FFCDD2
  **Attacker now has:**
  AccessKeyId    = ASIA...
  SecretKey      = xxxx...
  SessionToken   = xxxx...
  **Valid for: 1 hour from issuance**
end note

== Step 3 — Attack vectors with extracted credentials ==

group "VECTOR A — Data exfiltration (3 queries, <1 second, ~$0.001)"
  ATK -> TS : SELECT * FROM <TABLE_RT>\n(1.1M rows — 11 months history)
  TS --> ATK : water_level, flux, lat/lng,\nbattery, signal strength
  ATK -> TS : SELECT * FROM <TABLE_HOURLY>
  TS --> ATK : hourly production aggregates
  ATK -> TS : SELECT * FROM <TABLE_DAILY>
  TS --> ATK : daily production aggregates
  note over ATK #FFCDD2
    **Cannot query any other table**
    IAM scoped to exactly 3 ARNs
    AccessDenied on all others
  end note
end

group "VECTOR B — Cost abuse (SELECT loop, programmatic)"
  ATK -> TS : SELECT * loop at 1–5 req/sec\nusing extracted STS keys
  TS --> ATK : data + CumulativeBytesMetered\n(37.9MB per full scan)
  note over ATK #FFCDD2
    Cost: $0.00038 per full scan
    At 5 req/sec → $6.84/hour potential
    **Kill switch fires before this**
  end note
end

group "VECTOR C — S3 session log read"
  ATK -> S3 : ListBucket → enumerate all session files
  ATK -> S3 : GetObject → read other users' session logs
  note over ATK #FFCDD2
    Can read: emails, IPs, pages visited
    Cannot delete (s3:DeleteObject removed)
    Cannot write to any other bucket
  end note
end

== Step 4 — Layer 1 fires (~2 minutes after attack starts) ==

ATK -> TS : Query loop continues...
TS -> CT : Every API call logged\n(eventSource, eventName,\ncallerIdentity, timestamp)
CT -> CWL : Real-time log stream
CWL -> CWA : Metric Filter counts\nTimestream Query events
CWA -> CWA : Sum ≥ 50 in 5-min window\nNORMAL max: ~6/5min\nATTACK at 1/sec: 300/5min

CWA -> SNS : ALARM state → publish
SNS -> ADM : Email alert
SNS -> LAM : Invoke (automatic)

LAM -> UP : ListUsers
LAM -> UP : AdminListGroupsForUser\n(skip 'admin' group)
LAM -> UP : AdminUserGlobalSignOut\n→ all refresh tokens invalidated
LAM -> UP : AdminDisableUser\n→ login blocked

note over LAM #C8E6C9
  **Admin account: skipped entirely**
  All other pool users: locked
  Time from attack start: ~1–2 min
  Max cost before lockdown: ~$0.03
end note

ATK -> UP : Tries to refresh token
UP --> ATK : NotAuthorizedException\n(token invalidated)
ATK -> UP : Tries to re-login
UP --> ATK : UserNotConfirmedException\n(account disabled)

== Step 5 — Layer 2 fires (if Layer 1 somehow missed) ==

BUD -> BUD : Detects Timestream spend\napproaching $5\n(checked ~3x per day)
BUD -> ADM : Email at $4 (80% threshold)
BUD -> DENY : Attach deny policy to\n<AUTH_ROLE>
DENY -> TS : All timestream:* calls\n→ AccessDenied\n(existing STS tokens blocked immediately)
BUD -> SNS : $5 threshold → publish
SNS -> LAM : Invoke lockdown Lambda (again)

== Step 6 — STS credential expiry ==

note over ATK #FFCDD2
  Even if attacker avoids triggering alarms:
  STS credentials expire after **1 hour**
  Cannot be renewed (Cognito account disabled)
  New login impossible (account locked)
  **Attack window: max 1 hour**
end note

== TTL Summary ==

note over UP, IP #E3F2FD
  **Token TTLs:**
  idToken / accessToken  → 1 hour
  refreshToken           → 30 days (invalidated by AdminUserGlobalSignOut)
  STS credentials        → 1 hour hard limit (non-renewable after lockdown)
  CloudWatch alarm check → every 5 minutes
  AWS Budget check       → every ~8 hours
  Lambda execution       → ~3 seconds after SNS publish
end note

@enduml
